1
00:00:04,720 --> 00:00:09,942
Whenever you make 
an intellectual approach

2
00:00:09,942 --> 00:00:17,140
to Divine substance,
that can be the end result.

3
00:00:17,140 --> 00:00:19,384
It could be anything,
is the point.

4
00:00:19,668 --> 00:00:23,294
[The Gods are Bewildered]

5
00:00:23,794 --> 00:00:30,612
Kṛṣṇa consciousness’ beginning,
middle, and end is the culture of faith.

6
00:00:30,902 --> 00:00:35,204
So, that’s why Brahmā,

7
00:00:35,204 --> 00:00:40,839
He also had questions
that could not be answered.

8
00:00:41,749 --> 00:00:45,807
How can a five-year-old
cowherd boy …

9
00:00:45,887 --> 00:00:50,424
He doesn’t have 
four arms like Viṣṇu,

10
00:00:50,424 --> 00:00:54,594
He’s not carrying 
a giant scepter with jewels,

11
00:00:54,594 --> 00:01:00,672
He has a stick in His hand,
and a flute stuffed in His belt,

12
00:01:00,672 --> 00:01:05,454
and food in His left hand,
and He’s eating with His friends

13
00:01:05,454 --> 00:01:08,685
on the banks of the Jamunā.

14
00:01:10,175 --> 00:01:13,182
So, he has questions,
he’s going like,

15
00:01:13,182 --> 00:01:19,597
“How can that be God? 
I know Nārāyaṇ, he looks like God—

16
00:01:20,707 --> 00:01:25,870
four arms, 
crown, lot of aiśvarya,

17
00:01:25,870 --> 00:01:29,170
that sounds … 
seems to be God.”

18
00:01:29,170 --> 00:01:33,392
This is supposed …
All these grown adults

19
00:01:34,572 --> 00:01:39,686
bowing down to a little boy
with His stick.

20
00:01:39,686 --> 00:01:43,738
You’ve seen the sticks, 
that kind of stick.

21
00:01:43,738 --> 00:01:47,371
We see them, they still do it—
the little cowherd boys in India.

22
00:01:47,371 --> 00:01:53,527
They have a little stick, they tap
the calves with, for herding them.

23
00:01:53,527 --> 00:01:56,474
So He has a stick,
flute in the belt,

24
00:01:56,474 --> 00:02:01,952
food in the palm,
eating with His friends.

25
00:02:03,422 --> 00:02:07,186
So, muhyanti yat sūrayaḥ
[SB: 1.1.1],

26
00:02:07,186 --> 00:02:10,409
the Bhāgavatam tells you
in the beginning,

27
00:02:10,409 --> 00:02:16,384
“Gods are bewildered in trying
to understand Kṛṣṇa conception.”

28
00:02:16,384 --> 00:02:23,061
Brahmā-vimohan, Indra-mohan,
Mohinī-mūrti with Śiva.

29
00:02:23,061 --> 00:02:28,886
If we think, we are going to know
every last detail,

30
00:02:28,886 --> 00:02:32,380
then it’s not Kṛṣṇa conception.

31
00:02:33,550 --> 00:02:34,969
Saraswatī Ṭhākur said,

32
00:02:34,969 --> 00:02:43,302
“Then why He is called adhokṣaja,
adhaḥ akṣaja?”

33
00:02:43,302 --> 00:02:47,508
What are we told? Akṣaja—
the eyes, the senses;

34
00:02:47,508 --> 00:02:53,413
adhaḥ means, when He decides 
to reveal something of Himself to you,

35
00:02:53,413 --> 00:02:58,400
all your sense experience 
is pushed down,

36
00:02:58,400 --> 00:02:59,989
so that can happen.

37
00:02:59,989 --> 00:03:02,452
It’s suppressed.

38
00:03:03,292 --> 00:03:07,957
The inversion meaning—when you 
are in full-blown sense experience,

39
00:03:07,957 --> 00:03:09,782
what is Saraswatī Ṭhākur saying,

40
00:03:09,782 --> 00:03:14,169
“Trying to, like vultures,
looking for vulture food:

41
00:03:14,169 --> 00:03:15,975
the eyes want 
to devour something,

42
00:03:15,975 --> 00:03:18,975
the ears want
to hear the sweet sound,

43
00:03:18,975 --> 00:03:23,765
the tongue wants to taste …
Like vultures.”

44
00:03:23,765 --> 00:03:26,645
That’s why Guru Mahārāj said,
“Saraswatī Ṭhākur did not advise

45
00:03:26,645 --> 00:03:31,101
taking Kṛṣṇa-nām
before a picture of Kṛṣṇa”,

46
00:03:31,101 --> 00:03:32,086
which we could say,

47
00:03:32,086 --> 00:03:37,069
“Oh, many, if not most devotees,
they do something like that.

48
00:03:37,069 --> 00:03:41,482
Oh, but our param-guru,
or my param-guru,

49
00:03:41,482 --> 00:03:43,921
he’s saying not to do that.

50
00:03:43,921 --> 00:03:44,868
Why?”

51
00:03:44,868 --> 00:03:50,185
Your eyes will turn that image
of Kṛṣṇa into vulture food.

52
00:03:51,715 --> 00:03:54,748
When the artists asked Kṛṣṇa,

53
00:03:54,748 --> 00:03:58,719
“Is this what Kṛṣṇa really,
(that was Prabhupād)

54
00:03:58,719 --> 00:04:01,496
is this what Kṛṣṇa 
really looks like?”

55
00:04:01,496 --> 00:04:04,618
He said, “Not exactly,
but you’ll recognize Him,

56
00:04:04,618 --> 00:04:07,051
when you see Him.”

57
00:04:07,051 --> 00:04:11,335
Gopa Kumār, he recognizes
Kṛṣṇa when he sees Him.

